explains: adj. 不确定的；模糊的；含混的
wordGroup: statically indeterminate structure [化]超静定结构；静不定结构

sentences.en: She was a tall woman of indeterminate age.
sentences.cn: 她是个看不出年龄的高大女子。

sentences.en: I hope to carry on for an indeterminate period.
sentences.cn: 我希望在一段不确定的时间内这样继续下去。

sentences.en: One of the major limitations of CT screening is the number of screens in which a nodule or other indeterminate finding potentially related to lung cancer is found.
sentences.cn: CT成像的一个主要局限性在于要做几次扫描才能发现一个结节或其它可能与肺癌相关的异常。
